<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF4FFB5FC959F7F6D4B7E93" pageId="25" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF4FFB5FC959F7F6DB17E12" blockId="25.[831,1436,827,1011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF4FFB5FC959F7F6ABD7E32" bold="true" box="[831,944,827,851]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is distinguished by a slightly convex ventral side and a more convex dorsal side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF4FFB5FC959F3F6D4B7E93" blockId="25.[831,1436,827,1011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF4FFB5FC959F3F6D7F7EF2" bold="true" box="[831,1138,891,915]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the chalk of Wadi Mellaha and G. Duwi by NAKKADY (1950). It is found in the Maastrichtian and rarely in the Paleocene of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
